original: Jonsson, Enar Gustaf Nathanael, redaktör, Göteborg, f. 18/5/91 i Gbg av Gustaf J. o. Lovisa Börjesson. — Stud:ex. v. Gbgs h. latin 09. Tj :man i Skand. Kredit A-B 10-12, medarb. i Gbgs-Posten 13-16, i Gbgs Hand:- o. Sjöfartstidn. sed. 16. Medl. av Publ:-kl. o. Sv. journ:fören. Sign.: E. J., Fob m. fl.
translated: Jonsson, Enar Gustaf Nathanael, editor, Gothenburg, born May 18th, 1891 in Gothenburg to Gustaf J. and Lovisa Börjesson. He graduated from Gothenburg's Higher Latin School in 1909. He worked as a clerk at Skand. Kredit A-B from 1910-1912 and as a contributor to Gbgs-Posten from 1913-1916, and later at Gbgs Handel- och Sjöfartstidning. He is a member of the Publicist Club and the Swedish Journalist Association. He used the signature E.J., Fob and others. He married in the year 19xx, with the partner's name unknown.
